cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.CR 

The paper discusses a novel scalable distributed database system, which suggests it could belong to the cs.DB (database) sub-category. The focus on network technology and hardware provisioning also suggests it could belong to the cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) and cs.OS (operating systems) sub-categories. The mention of experiments with the TPC-C benchmark suggests it could also belong to the cs.CR (cryptography and security) sub-category. Finally, the paper's title and abstract suggest it could belong to the cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) sub-category.
